======================================================================
PART 2: Odd cycle pairing under anti-automorphism
======================================================================
Total odd directed cycles in T_7: 80
By length: [(3, 14), (5, 42), (7, 24)]

Anti-aut cycle pairing:
  Fixed (self-paired) cycles: 12
  Chiral pairs of cycles: 34
  Check: 12 + 2×34 = 80 (expected 80)

  Vertex-DISJOINT paired cycles: 1/34
  These contribute to α_2 in OCF: each disjoint pair contributes +4 to H

  OCF components:
  alpha_1 = 80 (total odd cycles)
  alpha_2 = 7 (disjoint pairs)
  H = I(Omega, 2) ≥ 1 + 2*80 + 4*7 = 189
  (This is a LOWER BOUND; full I(Omega,2) also counts alpha_3, alpha_4, ...)

